The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 BCCI allays fixing fears

New Delhi: The BCCI on Thursday allayed fears that its move to organise a series of one-day Internationals at neutral venues would see a repeat of match-fixing scandal. Earlier, there used to be middlemen who organised the events and the Board was paid an appearance money. But now, we will conduct the matches. We own the tournament and the rights are with us, BCCI marketing committee member I.S. Bindra said on Thursday. (PTI) 




